# GojoGo — Project Overview

SwiftUI iOS superapp (`com.gojogo.app`, iOS 17+, Swift 5). Dark-only (`preferredColorScheme(.dark)`). Bundle lives in `GojoGo/`.

## Folder map

| Folder | Role |
|---|---|
| `Auth/` | Welcome → email → onboarding steps |
| `DesignSystem/` | `GGColor`, fonts, glass modifiers, shared components |
| `Models/` | `AppState`, domain types, `SampleData` |
| `Navigation/` | `RootView`, `MainAppView`, `GGTabBar` |
| `Screens/` | Tab surfaces + shared screen UI |
| `Travel/` | Mapbox config for GojoTravel |

## State & flow

- Single source of truth: `@MainActor` `AppState` (`ObservableObject`), injected via `@EnvironmentObject`.
- Auth gated by `app.phase`: `.welcome` → `.email` → `.onboarding` → `.app`.
- Main tabs via `app.activeTab`: `.home`, `.watch`, `.madeleine`, `.travel`, `.economy`, `.search`.
- Sheets/covers: `showProfile`, `showWatching`. Watch sub-feed: `watchSubFeed` (Feed / Shorts / TV).
- GojoTravel: `travelPhase` (home → searching → choosingRide → matching → enRoute → inTrip → completed).

```swift
// ✅ Drive UI from AppState
withAnimation(.easeInOut(duration: 0.35)) { app.phase = .email }

// ❌ Don't invent parallel navigation stacks or new global stores
```

## Naming

- Prefix shared design tokens/components with `GG` (`GGColor`, `GGTabBar`, `GGUser`, `GGBackground`).
- Views are `*View` structs in the folder that owns the flow.
- Prefer extending existing files over new one-off helpers unless the concern is clearly new.
---

## Content

UI is mostly prototype/sample-driven (`SampleData`). Keep models in `Models.swift`; mock content in `SampleData.swift`. No backend layer yet — don't add networking unless asked.
